 "Full Actors-pattern implementation (Governor + MarketEntry-LLM mock advisor + langgraph-clj StateGraph + append-only audit ledger + MemStore/DatomicStore), adapted from the cloud-itonami-iso3166-ago reference implementation: src/marketentry/{facts,governor,registry,store,marketentryllm,operation,phase}.cljc + full test suite (governor contract, store contract MemStore≡DatomicStore parity, registry pure-function, phase, facts) + docs/business-model.md + docs/operator-guide.md. The jurisdiction dossier (marketentry.facts) is intentionally THINNER and more conservative than several sibling jurisdictions (e.g. AGO, FJI): the verified research dossier (finance.gov.tv, tuvalu-legislation.tv, WIPO Lex) found no national e-procurement portal and no independently-verifiable distinct tax-ID scheme for Tuvalu, so :national-spec says so honestly rather than inventing either, the governor is SIX checks (not AGO's seven -- no analog of AGO's nif-unverified check, since the dossier does not ground a distinct TUV tax-ID scheme), and the demo engagement set is 5 engagements (not AGO's 6). What IS verified and cited in facts.cljc: the Public Procurement Act CAP 4.21 (2022 Revised Edition) as procurement legal basis, a Central Procurement Unit within the Ministry of Finance and Economic Development as procurement administering body, and the Companies and Business Registration Act (CAP 40.12, 2008 Revised Edition) as the flagship check's business-registration legal basis (business-registration-missing check, requires-tuv-registration?/has-tuv-registration?)."}
